				<p>
					Blockchain, it might be a term you have heard before but didn’t understand. Most people relate the term “Blockchain” to 							cryptocurrencies like Bitcoin, Onecoin, Buxcoin, etc. 
				</p>

				<p>
					Modern technology allows people to communicate directly via calls, emails, pictures, as well as messages travel instantly from one device to another this allows for the individuals using the service to maintain trust between one another that their information is safe. Conversely, when it comes to financial transactions people need to trust a third party to complete a transaction, with Blockchain everything is changing. Blockchain uses high-level Mathematics and Cryptography to create an “Open Decentralized Database for the transaction of any value”. This allows it to create a database that can be verified by anyone with an internet connection.

				</p>
