				<p>
					Blockchain can be implemented anywhere where there is a value being transferred, for example, voting, property transfer, money transfer, digital goods, etc. Blockchain can change how transactions work as it will no longer occur through a third party, making third parties obsolete. 
				</p>
				
				
				<p>
					Blockchain is special and is different from other technologies out there because of the way it stores and transfers the value. It uses “an open decentralized database” which can be accessed by anyone but allows for maximum safety as the way Blockchain stores data is different as it separates the data onto different computers from around the world connected by the internet if one of the computers were to get compromised in a cyber-attack the other computers will still be secure and will not allow for the data to get stolen as a decryption key will be required, hence protecting the user data.
				</p>
				<p>
					There are still quite a few drawbacks to the technology, the technology is so secure that even governments themselves can see what is happening and can’t protect their citizens from a Blockchain scam. Governments will struggle to moderate Blockchain transactions which could lead to massive scams. 
				</p>
				<p>
					Overall, in my opinion, Blockchain is a technology that may replace common methods of value transfer in a few years but will require a bit of tweaking before governments can fully accept Blockchain as an actual transaction method. 
